[F]The air is sweet as Melva's [G]wine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
And I sip her wine and I listen to the robin sings
[F]And the river runs through Kingston [G]Springs
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Every year about this time
[F]A few ol' friends come up the [G]walk
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
Every year about this time
[F]A few ol' friends stop by to [G]talk
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
And we talk about the crops and weather and things
[F]And the young folks here in Kingston [G]Springs
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
[F]I've got a brother up Chicago way
[G]He wants me to visit him [Em]someday and I may [Am]sometimes
[F]But not as long as the robin sings
[G]And the river runs through Kingston Springs
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
It was last year about this time
[F]Melva made her last batch of [G]wine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
